{{DISPLAYTITLE: <span style="font-family:Centaur; color:#e2131b; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #f5222a"> Level 750: '''''Ambient Emotions'''''</span>}}

{{Audio|file=The Singing Halls .mp3|volume=1|secrettext=refresh page|align=center}}
<center>'''''Have a good time...'''''</center> 
==<span style="font-family: Centaur; color:#fff9f9; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #f1f1f1">'''''Overview'''''</span>==

Level 750 is a level based on ambience, the character and atmosphere of anywhere at anytime. This level has approximately six distinct variations of these, all with their own unique range of feelings that encompass the wanderer should they walk into any of these ambiences. It is easy identify one of these seven ambiences, as they all each have their own unique light that encompasses them as they are often at times bright.

The brightness of these lights ranges from very dim to very bright. Very dim making the wanderer feel very little of the present ambience, while very bright making the wanderer making the most of the ambience, even if it turns them into a '''Binding Angel'''. The very bright lights are the most common ones throughout the level, while very dim lights are the rarest. Wanderers who manage to exit the level often have slim segments of their memories permanently altered, often with a single emotion being more prevalent in them when they exit the level.

==<span style="font-family: Centaur; color:#fff9f9; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #f1f1f1">'''''Phsyical Interior'''''</span>==

The physical interior of the level is remanent of various interior spaces, mainly from decades of the 1940s all the way until the early 1990s. The floors are made of 1960s carpet and although there are some areas of decay where the carpet has rotted, it is intact and safe to walk on, even on the rotted areas of the carpet. There are several areas with stairs, each leading to additional areas that feature the same things as from where you came from originally. 

There are two types of areas in the level, though they are just slightly different from each other, containing mostly the same features as the ones listed previously. Though they are somewhat aesthetically different from each other in some ways, and the decals and styles of these two areas are different enough to classify them on their own.
{{Blurimage|file=The Classic Area.png||caption=A image of The Classic Area without the lights on.|align=right}}
'''The Classic Area''' is the older style of the two, with it being more of the 1940s and 1950s style of architecture and having slightly less lights than the other area. Despite having less lights, it has more bright lights than its other counterpart. The carpets in this area have more of an abundance of rotted carpet but less stairs than the other area.
{{Blurimage|file=The Middle Area.png||caption=A image of a portion of The Middle Area in a melancholic emotional ambience.|align=right}}
'''The Middle Area''' is the newer style of the two, with it having mix of 1960s, 1970s, 1980s, and early 1990s styles of architecture, decor, and has more lights than its counterpart. Despite having more lights, they have more of a chance to be dim than the other area. The carpets in this area have less of the rotted carpet.

==<span style="font-family: Centaur; color:#fff9f9; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #f1f1f1">'''''Ambiences'''''</span>==

Ambiences are all around the wanderers in this level, with high rates of wanderers in any of the two states on this level. There is a total of six ambiences in the level, each with their own Mild and Extreme states. Each ambience can be easily identified with their own light colors, which range from Very Dim to Very Bright. The effects of ambiences on wanderers are extremely dangerous and will almost result in them becoming a '''Binding Angel'''. 

'''The Mild State''' is one in which the wanderer is slightly affected by ambiences. This is the preferred state to be in during normal time and is the safest one can be in until '''The Basic State''' occurs. The effects of all ambiences are dimmed by around half, quarter, or somewhere in between. The wanderer's body will still be forced to feel the ambiences, but they will have more subconscious than in '''The Ambient State'''. One can be in '''The Mild State''' if the lights above are Very Dim, Dim, or slightly bright.
{{Blurimage|file=Ambience Emotional Chart.png|caption=A chart displaying the light colors of each emotional ambience.|align=right}}
'''The Ambient State''' is the most dangerous state to be in, as it is the one the wanderer has the least amount of subconsciousness and the most prone to being a '''Binding Angel''' or a puppet of '''Mr. Altman'''. It is in this state that wanderers are fully exposed to the ambiences and if bright enough, can overwhelm them. One can be in the state if the lights above are bright, very bright, and extremely bright.

There are a total of six ambiences, and they each have their own variations of '''The Mild State''' and '''The Ambient State'''. They all each have their own unique light colors as well. All ambiences are connected to emotions one can express themselves with. These emotional ambiences have shown to temporarily, or sometimes permanently damage wanderers mental states. 

===<span style="font-family: Centaur; color:#FAFA04; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #FFFF67">'''''𝓔𝓾𝓹𝓱𝓸𝓻𝓲𝓪'''''</span>===

'''Mild State:''' When one enters mild euphoria, one will feel happy. Positive memories will circulate throughout their minds on loop. Their physical expressions will resemble that of happy faces and will look in awe at what surrounds them, falsely imagining that they are in a happy place. Wanderers will also be forced to smile all the time while in this state and '''The Ambient State''', though to a lesser extent in this state. Their memories can also be fabricated if necessary and even if they exit the euphoric state, fragments of said memories can linger. 

'''Ambient State:''' When one enters total euphoria, positive memories will circulate faster, and fabricated memories will be created, regardless of the necessity of it. The bodies of wanderers themselves will also start to glow yellow, and their expressions will be in total ''Euphoria''. In this state, they will start to be forced to "Jump for joy", a never-ending cycle of leaping in the air. Their eyes will never blink in this state, and tears of joy will be appearing from the eyes. 

===<span style="font-family: Destroy X; color:#0801B0; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #0C03FF">'''''Melancholy'''''</span>===

'''Mild State:''' When one enters mild melancholy, one will feel sad. Feelings of sorrow will linger in the minds of wanderers and will trigger mild crying. The wanderer's physical expressions will show of sad faces and when looking at others, will imagine them crying along with themselves. Wanderers in this state will have twisted versions of their memories that will make them cry, often taking happy memories and distorting them to make them appear sad.

'''Ambient State:''' When one enters total Melancholy, they will experience even more twisted versions of their memories. Wanderers in this state will be forced to weep, with a never-ending amount of tears coming out of their eyes. This will strain the wanderer's eyes and make them cry even more, creating a cycle of pain that lasts for around 15 minutes. 

===<span style="font-family: Rubik Glitch; color:#F80B0B; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #DD2B2B">'''''Wrath'''''</span>===

'''Mild State:''' When one enters mild wrath, one will feel mad. Feelings of anger will persist in the minds of wanderers and can make their faces seem hateful to other wanderers around them if they are around. When one is in this state and when there are other wanderers around, the wanderer will have an illusion of either the others faces looking at them in disgust or wanderers face will not be there in general, signaling to the illusioned wanderer that they secretly hate them behind their back.

'''Ambient State:''' When one enters total wrath, they will feel total anger and will run around screaming. Memories will frequently appear in the wanderer's mind showing them past memories of them being bullied, insulted, and/or whatever makes them angrier and more hateful to everyone around them. False memories will also appear in this state, planted in the mind by the light. These memories show anyone the wanderer loved and/or liked insulting them in various ways, cursing at them, and on rare occasions, show the wanderers themselves getting them physically beaten up by them. 
===<span style="font-family: Distressed Typewriter; color:#A100A1; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #6A0DAD">'''''Paranoia'''''</span>===

'''Mild State:''' When one enters mild Paranoia they feel as if they are afraid, that they fear something. The mind of the wanderer will never figure out what that fear is, but it will always be present in this ambience. In this state, they will be constantly wanting to move around. They will always look behind their backs every 5-10 seconds. 

'''Ambient State:''' When one enters total Paranoia, they will be in a state of total panic. They will grow even more afraid of their fabricated fears, to the point that their minds will start hallucinating around themes. Their memories will start to be twisted into thinking they have been afraid of that fear their whole lives and if one is in a group that they are but a manifestation of that fear.

===<span style="font-family: Broadway; color:#288a1d; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #24e80e">'''''Revulsion'''''</span>===

'''Mild State:''' When one enters mild Revulsion, they will feel disgusted at everything around them. Their minds will perceive anything around them as if it wrong to them. They will begin to feel disgusted at their own bodies, hating what they look like and wanting a desire for a change in themselves and everything around them.

'''Ambient State:''' When one enters total Revulsion, they will start to have illusions of decay around them. They will hallucinate that the walls around them are beginning to rot away, everything around them decaying. This includes their own bodies. They will start to see themselves age over and over again, and will see some parts of themselves rotting away.

===<span style="font-family: Courier New; color:#666666; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #a2a3a2">'''''Apathy'''''</span>===

'''Mild State:''' When one enters mild Apathy, they have a lack of will to do anything much. They will move around slowly, walking around in a tired-like state. They will ignore some stuff around them, only noticing things when it is loud enough or It's close enough in their view. Even when they see another wanderer in another state, Mild or Ambient, they will react mildly to them both.

'''Ambient State:''' When one enters Full Apathy, they will have a total lack of emotions at all. They will walk upright, but will not react to anything at all, even when in danger. They will not hear anything or see anything in their point of view. They will oftern at times also just stop completely and stand still, not having any thoughts at all.

==<span style="font-family: Centaur; color:#fff9f9; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #f1f1f1">'''''Entities'''''</span>==

===<span style="font-family: Centaur; color:#fff9f9; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #f1f1f1">'''''The Binding Angels'''''</span>===

The Binding Angels are common hostile entities in level 987. They all are wearing fancy clothes, and all have large wings in their backs. Most of them are female, though it is rumored that male Binding Angels do exist. They mostly appear in '''The Middle Area''', though they will pop up in '''The Classic Area''' rarely. They will rarely ever talk, but if they do it will be addressed in the matter of what ambience they are tied with.

All Binding Angels all are tailored to a specific emotion, never in a mild state. They are however more aware of what they are feeling and will want to take out their emotions on wanderers. They will however sometimes hesitate to do anything to wanderers at all, even speaking that they want to be free. 

It has been confirmed that all Binding Angels are former wanderers turned entities. How they are transformed into Binding Angels are not known, but it is confirmed that '''Mr. Altman''' is the one behind it as it seems that there are more in numbers whenever he is nearby. 


===<span style="font-family: Centaur; color:#fff9f9; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #f1f1f1">'''''Mr. Altman'''''</span>===

Mr. Altman is a creature in level 750 that is mostly found in '''The Classic Area'''. He is a figure that stands around seven foot tall and dresses in an entirely black suit. Instead of a head, he has a sphere with several colorful eyes for a head. All of the eyes are colored the colors of each emotional ambience in the level. 

He is a very hostile entity and will attack anyone on sight. He will use his eyes to force an emotional ambience of his choosing onto them in order to stop them. He only uses this in rare scenarios however when one is close enough to him. Otherwise, he will just count on the Binding Angels to stop wanderers in their tracks and to bring them to him. 

Once one is captured either by him or a Binding Angel, he will transform them into a Binding Angel themselves. How he chooses the emotional ambience they use or why is unknown but is theorized by some that he studies the minds of those captured and picks an emotional ambience that suits them best.

==<span style="font-family: Centaur; color:#fff9f9; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #f1f1f1">'''''Groups and Organizations'''''</span>==

Due to the nature of this level, colonies and outposts cannot be established.

==<span style="font-family: Centaur; color:#fff9f9; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #f1f1f1">'''''Entrances and Exits'''''</span>==

===<span style="font-family: Centaur; color:#fff9f9; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #f1f1f1">'''''Entrances'''''</span>===

If one trips in [[Level 249]] below a purple light and pass out, they will wake up here.

If hallways in [[Level 986]] start to flicker in the emotional ambience colors, and one comes across a wooden door and enters it, they will be brought here.

If a yellow mist appears in [[Level 440]] and one walks through it, they will be brought here.

if one finds an orange antique film reel in [[Level 501]] and pick it up, they will fall asleep and wake up here. 

===<span style="font-family: Centaur; color:#fff9f9; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #f1f1f1">'''''Exits'''''</span>===

If one finds a section in The Classic Area where no emotional ambience lights are present and finds a black door, enter it and they will be brought to [[Level 988]].

If one travels five miles in the level, in The Middle Area, one can find a glass drink with a blue liquid. Drink it, and one will fall asleep and wake up in [[Level 255]].

If one manages to find an amusement park ticket at any point in the level and walk one mile in the level after picking it up, they will come across a ticket booth. Insert the ticket into a tray in front of the ticket booth, they will be brought to [[Level 320]].

